00:02:22.600 --> 00:02:23.160
(Previously)

00:02:23.160 --> 00:02:24.290
(Previously)
It's not just a near miss,

00:02:24.590 --> 00:02:26.010
I think I'm about to collide
with you for real.

00:02:27.920 --> 00:02:28.420
Ping,

00:02:28.960 --> 00:02:30.690
I think we should keep some distance for now.

00:02:30.820 --> 00:02:32.060
But I'm sorry...

00:02:32.800 --> 00:02:34.030
for crossing the line too much.

00:02:35.660 --> 00:02:36.890
Didn't you say you wanted to

00:02:37.270 --> 00:02:38.880
recheck your own feelings first?

00:02:39.610 --> 00:02:40.770
Maybe

00:02:41.340 --> 00:02:43.290
I was just trying to use him to replace Namhom.

00:02:43.740 --> 00:02:45.720
You're not trying to avoid me, are you?

00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:47.190
Yes,

00:02:47.610 --> 00:02:49.020
I really am avoiding you.

00:02:49.370 --> 00:02:50.020
From now on,

00:02:50.730 --> 00:02:52.810
I'll personally take charge of Nawa's safety.

00:02:54.070 --> 00:02:55.350
Are you sure it's okay

00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:57.540
for you to sneak out at this hour?

00:02:58.080 --> 00:02:59.640
But I couldn't stand missing you anymore.

00:03:00.190 --> 00:03:01.560
I still want to be with you.

00:03:02.410 --> 00:03:03.020
Nawa,

00:03:03.420 --> 00:03:04.830
If you walk away with him right now,

00:03:06.160 --> 00:03:07.200
you'll never see me again.

00:03:08.540 --> 00:03:10.510
Can I talk to you Phraphai alone?

00:03:10.970 --> 00:03:13.370
I'm sorry, Phraphai,
for talking to you this way…

00:03:14.570 --> 00:03:15.920
I've fallen in love with Mr. Phurit.

00:03:16.660 --> 00:03:18.360
Please let me follow my heart.

00:03:19.740 --> 00:03:20.130
Huh?

00:03:21.960 --> 00:03:23.090
Who came looking for me?

00:03:26.030 --> 00:03:27.560
You told me

00:03:27.840 --> 00:03:29.170
you had a huge fight with Ping.

00:03:30.160 --> 00:03:31.090
My guess is…

00:03:32.030 --> 00:03:33.410
he's probably just feeling hurt.

00:03:35.590 --> 00:03:36.560
I think maybe…

00:03:37.750 --> 00:03:39.770
tonight, or tomorrow, he might...

00:03:39.770 --> 00:03:40.900
It has to be tonight.

00:03:41.240 --> 00:03:42.190
It has to be tonight.

00:03:42.580 --> 00:03:44.220
If I don't see Ping tonight…

00:03:44.220 --> 00:03:45.730
I'll never see him again.

00:03:46.800 --> 00:03:49.390
Never see him again?
What do you mean by that?

00:03:50.180 --> 00:03:51.570
What do you mean it has to be tonight?

00:03:57.440 --> 00:03:58.610
Today's gonna be rough.

00:03:59.130 --> 00:04:01.040
Ping's off, and Nawa's not here either.

00:04:02.330 --> 00:04:03.460
I don't get your mom.

00:04:03.740 --> 00:04:05.380
Why'd she have to take Nawa out
for errands today?

00:04:22.190 --> 00:04:23.560
Tonight's a full moon.

00:04:25.600 --> 00:04:26.140
Ma'am...

00:04:27.420 --> 00:04:28.260
is Ping a merman?

00:04:33.290 --> 00:04:36.400
If you manage to reach Ping,
please call me right away.

00:04:36.970 --> 00:04:38.110
My brother's a merman too.

00:04:39.120 --> 00:04:39.900
I know what happens

00:04:40.330 --> 00:04:42.380
if they don't purge the poison tonight.

00:04:44.090 --> 00:04:45.580
If you tell me the truth,

00:04:46.600 --> 00:04:48.280
it might help me find him faster.

00:04:52.760 --> 00:04:53.520
Ma'am…

00:04:55.070 --> 00:04:56.890
There's something I need to confess.

00:05:02.040 --> 00:05:02.980
I'm in love with your son.

00:05:06.570 --> 00:05:09.680
And honestly, this is something
I should be saying to him,

00:05:10.380 --> 00:05:11.490
not to you.

00:05:13.640 --> 00:05:16.770
But right now,
I don't care if Ping's human

00:05:17.240 --> 00:05:18.080
or merman,

00:05:19.740 --> 00:05:21.290
I just don't want him to disappear.

00:05:22.610 --> 00:05:24.540
If I never get to tell him this myself,

00:05:25.550 --> 00:05:27.220
I'll hate myself for the rest of my life.

00:05:33.690 --> 00:05:34.380
It's my fault…

00:05:35.750 --> 00:05:37.180
It's all my fault.

00:05:40.510 --> 00:05:41.690
Please, calm down, ma'am.

00:05:48.480 --> 00:05:50.300
Please calm down first.

00:05:52.300 --> 00:05:54.930
What matters is finding Ping.

00:05:56.850 --> 00:05:58.460
You can tell me everything in the car.

00:06:01.210 --> 00:06:02.360
Thank you.

00:06:02.960 --> 00:06:03.970
Thank you so much.

00:06:12.850 --> 00:06:13.400
Dad!

00:06:16.880 --> 00:06:17.370
Dad!

00:06:18.920 --> 00:06:19.410
Dad!

00:06:37.270 --> 00:06:39.420
Who did this to you?

00:06:39.760 --> 00:06:40.680
Who?

00:06:53.480 --> 00:06:54.930
Was it the humans?

00:06:56.770 --> 00:06:58.140
I'll handle this myself.

00:06:58.730 --> 00:06:59.950
Calm down, Phraphai.

00:07:01.530 --> 00:07:03.130
What happened to your father

00:07:04.190 --> 00:07:05.850
has nothing to do with the concession deal.

00:07:07.990 --> 00:07:09.890
What do you mean by that, Grandpa?

00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:12.780
The humans who came to hunt mermen,

00:07:14.320 --> 00:07:16.430
the headman already dealt with them.

00:07:17.130 --> 00:07:18.730
The person who killed him…

00:07:19.410 --> 00:07:22.300
was someone your father
had business conflicts with.

00:07:23.350 --> 00:07:25.740
Let the police handle it by the law.

00:07:27.230 --> 00:07:29.710
Grandpa Samut,
stop defending those damn humans!

00:07:31.130 --> 00:07:33.600
Didn't you see?
They killed my father!

00:07:34.940 --> 00:07:36.440
Just tell me who it was,

00:07:37.420 --> 00:07:39.640
I'll show them not to mess with mermen.

00:07:40.420 --> 00:07:44.230
The one who killed your father
was a merman.

00:07:54.340 --> 00:07:57.420
You should've known your father better.

00:08:00.040 --> 00:08:01.580
Before you came,

00:08:02.550 --> 00:08:03.900
we found proof

00:08:04.640 --> 00:08:07.840
of all the terrible things
he'd done to the culprit.

00:08:09.140 --> 00:08:10.520
They're not so different.

00:08:13.610 --> 00:08:17.290
Now,
if you're truly choosing not to seek revenge,

00:08:17.720 --> 00:08:18.740
then

00:08:20.090 --> 00:08:22.590
there's something you should know…

00:08:23.730 --> 00:08:25.660
about what happened 20 years ago.

00:08:51.200 --> 00:08:52.660
I was so happy today.

00:08:53.980 --> 00:08:55.130
We spent the whole day together.

00:09:51.960 --> 00:09:52.560
Nawa.

00:10:01.460 --> 00:10:02.370
Where are you going?

00:10:05.310 --> 00:10:06.440
Are you not feeling well?

00:10:10.790 --> 00:10:14.510
Tonight…
there's somewhere I need to go.

00:10:16.420 --> 00:10:19.090
Where? Let me go with you.

00:10:23.730 --> 00:10:24.530
It's fine.

00:10:27.040 --> 00:10:28.480
I'll be quick, I'll come right back.

00:10:35.830 --> 00:10:37.340
Are you hiding something from me?

00:10:40.380 --> 00:10:43.970
You know what hurts me the most?

00:10:44.690 --> 00:10:47.760
That even you treat me like an outsider.

00:10:49.150 --> 00:10:50.990
You never tell me anything,
you never let me understand.

00:11:00.950 --> 00:11:01.720
Mr. Phurit.

00:11:05.140 --> 00:11:06.870
If I tell you the truth,

00:11:08.990 --> 00:11:10.300
can you promise me one thing?

00:11:13.570 --> 00:11:14.910
Promise you won't leave me.

00:11:21.780 --> 00:11:22.420
Nawa…

00:11:24.520 --> 00:11:25.530
I don't know

00:11:26.460 --> 00:11:28.490
what you're about to tell me,

00:11:32.490 --> 00:11:33.730
but I promise

00:11:35.780 --> 00:11:37.160
I'll stay by your side no matter what.

00:11:50.410 --> 00:11:51.060
Nawa!

00:11:54.280 --> 00:11:54.940
Back off.

00:11:55.520 --> 00:11:56.780
I don't have time to explain!

00:11:57.610 --> 00:11:58.250
Phraphai!

00:11:59.060 --> 00:11:59.960
Calm down!

00:12:00.320 --> 00:12:01.700
What's wrong with Nawa?

00:12:02.720 --> 00:12:04.040
You're going to kill Nawa.

00:12:05.010 --> 00:12:05.940
Phraphai.

00:12:09.060 --> 00:12:10.190
My father just passed away today.

00:12:10.940 --> 00:12:12.350
I can't lose you too.

00:12:32.390 --> 00:12:34.130
I think we should keep some distance for now.

00:12:35.270 --> 00:12:36.980
I feel like we've gotten too close.

00:12:37.790 --> 00:12:38.990
I'm worried about what people might think.

00:12:45.360 --> 00:12:45.970
Ping!

00:12:48.220 --> 00:12:48.900
Phana!

00:12:52.910 --> 00:12:54.540
I've been looking everywhere for you.

00:12:55.480 --> 00:12:57.260
Your mom came to the shop

00:12:57.810 --> 00:12:59.490
and told me everything.

00:13:00.730 --> 00:13:01.600
My mom?

00:13:05.040 --> 00:13:06.940
She's so worried about you, you know?

00:13:09.910 --> 00:13:11.590
Can I ask you something straight?

00:13:12.290 --> 00:13:13.540
Since the day I was born,

00:13:14.800 --> 00:13:16.150
have you ever loved me?

00:13:17.210 --> 00:13:18.670
If you hate me that much,

00:13:19.370 --> 00:13:20.980
why don't you just kill me?

00:13:29.930 --> 00:13:31.690
If I walk out of your life right now,

00:13:33.010 --> 00:13:34.500
will that make you happy?

00:13:36.140 --> 00:13:37.340
Go wherever you want.

00:13:37.890 --> 00:13:39.260
I don't want anything to do with you anymore.

00:13:42.830 --> 00:13:43.800
That's impossible.

00:13:48.290 --> 00:13:50.170
She feels guilty, Ping.

00:13:52.210 --> 00:13:56.220
The moment she realized
you might never come back,

00:13:58.340 --> 00:14:00.040
she finally understood.

00:14:01.030 --> 00:14:02.590
She realized you've always been her everything.

00:14:09.940 --> 00:14:11.040
I'm sorry, Ping.

00:14:12.890 --> 00:14:16.970
For avoiding you,

00:14:18.250 --> 00:14:19.680
for being cold to you.

00:14:21.700 --> 00:14:22.520
Actually,

00:14:24.380 --> 00:14:26.790
I just wanted to be sure
of my feelings toward you.

00:14:29.240 --> 00:14:30.780
I want to be able to say confidently

00:14:32.420 --> 00:14:34.010
that you're not a replacement for anyone.

00:14:37.120 --> 00:14:38.130
But because…

00:14:40.010 --> 00:14:41.140
I really do love you.

00:15:14.180 --> 00:15:15.360
I love you so much.

00:15:17.850 --> 00:15:19.340
Even if it took me too long to realize.

00:15:22.320 --> 00:15:23.960
I love you so much, Ping.

00:15:45.700 --> 00:15:47.600
Phana…

00:15:48.450 --> 00:15:51.820
when you said my mom
told you everything…

00:15:53.810 --> 00:15:55.740
Does that mean you know that I...

00:15:56.300 --> 00:15:57.720
That you're a merman?

00:15:59.670 --> 00:16:01.150
I don't know if you know

00:16:02.020 --> 00:16:03.230
that Nawa's a merman too.

00:16:06.110 --> 00:16:07.380
So you already knew, huh.

00:16:09.130 --> 00:16:11.420
You know, to me,

00:16:12.340 --> 00:16:14.850
there's no real difference between
mermen and humans.

00:16:16.420 --> 00:16:18.210
We're just born in different kinds.

00:16:20.020 --> 00:16:22.370
But it is because of the stories
from the past that we have heard,

00:16:23.920 --> 00:16:25.560
that made me believe

00:16:27.360 --> 00:16:28.840
our kinds shouldn't love each other.

00:16:31.620 --> 00:16:33.460
That's why I kept trying to keep
Phurit and Nawa apart.

00:16:35.420 --> 00:16:36.590
But...

00:16:38.180 --> 00:16:41.750
once it happened to me…
I stopped caring about all that.

00:16:44.330 --> 00:16:46.130
I just want you to stay by my side.

00:16:48.060 --> 00:16:49.250
Don't disappear again.

00:17:09.580 --> 00:17:10.880
Are you sure, Phana?

00:17:12.910 --> 00:17:13.540
Yeah.

00:17:15.040 --> 00:17:16.360
Go cleanse off the poison,

00:17:17.900 --> 00:17:19.320
then come back with me.

00:17:20.750 --> 00:17:22.520
Your mom's waiting for you too.

00:17:25.150 --> 00:17:28.640
Give me another chance, for me, for her,

00:17:30.060 --> 00:17:31.690
and for yourself.

00:18:06.980 --> 00:18:08.150
Hey! What the hell are you doing?

00:18:27.740 --> 00:18:28.560
On this island,

00:18:29.830 --> 00:18:30.910
there are still a lot of

00:18:31.660 --> 00:18:33.030
complicated things going on

00:18:34.380 --> 00:18:36.390
and I can't tell you everything.

00:18:41.370 --> 00:18:43.480
I believe they really once
lived here on Khen Island.

00:18:45.890 --> 00:18:47.080
But probably not anymore.

00:18:48.560 --> 00:18:49.650
And I also believe that

00:18:51.260 --> 00:18:52.910
mermen and humans can never coexist.

00:18:54.400 --> 00:18:56.450
They say there are still mermen living

00:18:56.450 --> 00:18:58.020
among us on Khen Island.

00:18:58.620 --> 00:19:01.320
They look and act just like humans.

00:19:02.110 --> 00:19:03.290
Do no one can tell the difference.

00:19:03.760 --> 00:19:05.630
On the night before the full moon,

00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:06.690
every mermaid shows an

00:19:06.880 --> 00:19:09.710
eight-pointed star mark on their body.

00:19:10.410 --> 00:19:11.630
Before the full moon night?

00:19:11.660 --> 00:19:12.730
- Yes.
- Yeah.

00:19:24.930 --> 00:19:26.020
Did you get a tattoo?

00:19:28.740 --> 00:19:30.820
If they stay in human form

00:19:30.840 --> 00:19:32.610
for too long,

00:19:33.860 --> 00:19:36.410
marks begin to appear on their bodies,

00:19:36.410 --> 00:19:37.440
like tattoos.

00:19:38.390 --> 00:19:39.880
Before the full moon night.

00:19:40.300 --> 00:19:41.570
Those marks I mentioned

00:19:41.700 --> 00:19:43.280
are a warning.

00:19:43.600 --> 00:19:46.450
It means their blood is turning poisonous.

00:19:47.520 --> 00:19:48.850
And during that time,

00:19:48.950 --> 00:19:50.890
they must not mate with anyone.

00:19:51.830 --> 00:19:55.110
They have to dive deep into the ocean

00:19:55.490 --> 00:19:57.000
on the night of the full moon

00:19:57.890 --> 00:20:00.300
and cleanse their blood with coral.

00:20:01.170 --> 00:20:02.730
If they don't,

00:20:02.870 --> 00:20:05.450
they'll be trapped in mermen form forever.

00:20:06.500 --> 00:20:07.310
Mr. Phurit.

00:20:08.760 --> 00:20:10.570
If I tell you the truth,

00:20:12.780 --> 00:20:14.290
can you promise me one thing?

00:20:17.420 --> 00:20:18.730
Promise you won't leave me.

00:20:43.080 --> 00:20:43.970
Honestly,

00:20:44.900 --> 00:20:46.840
I'd love to see you swim, Ping.

00:20:47.690 --> 00:20:48.590
You'd be beautiful.

00:20:52.910 --> 00:20:53.750
What's the matter?

00:20:56.330 --> 00:20:57.170
That's strange.

00:20:58.180 --> 00:20:59.710
Never thought I'd hear something like this.

00:21:00.720 --> 00:21:03.820
I used to think of myself as a monster.

00:21:08.380 --> 00:21:10.990
From now on, don't think that again.

00:21:12.430 --> 00:21:13.520
To me,

00:21:16.240 --> 00:21:17.580
you're the most beautiful thing.

00:21:19.580 --> 00:21:21.790
And I want you to see yourself that way too.

00:21:33.160 --> 00:21:35.690
When you called my mom
and told her you found me…

00:21:36.600 --> 00:21:37.880
did she say anything?

00:21:39.660 --> 00:21:42.090
She just kept thanking me.

00:21:43.480 --> 00:21:46.780
I told her to go home and rest,

00:21:47.910 --> 00:21:49.780
and I'd bring you home tomorrow.

00:21:56.410 --> 00:21:57.270
What's on your mind?

00:22:00.650 --> 00:22:01.410
I don't know.

00:22:02.930 --> 00:22:04.360
I don't know if I can believe it.

00:22:06.040 --> 00:22:07.560
Ever since my dad died,

00:22:08.560 --> 00:22:10.190
my mom and I have grown more distant.

00:22:11.600 --> 00:22:12.710
In the past,

00:22:13.810 --> 00:22:15.520
it always felt like she found me disgusting.

00:22:18.990 --> 00:22:22.900
I don't know
what happened between you two,

00:22:24.460 --> 00:22:27.260
but I believe that from now on,

00:22:28.090 --> 00:22:29.630
she's not the same person she was before.

00:22:33.180 --> 00:22:36.130
Thank you.

00:24:33.450 --> 00:24:34.510
What's going on, Phu?

00:24:49.100 --> 00:24:50.060
What happened, Phu?

00:24:55.480 --> 00:24:57.060
You knew that Nawa's a merman, right?

00:25:00.760 --> 00:25:03.110
Yeah. You found out already?

00:25:03.860 --> 00:25:05.150
Then why the hell didn't you tell me?

00:25:06.670 --> 00:25:07.550
Why not?

00:25:10.060 --> 00:25:12.200
- Why?
- Mr. Phurit, please calm down!

00:25:13.180 --> 00:25:14.370
I can't calm down, Ping!

00:25:16.050 --> 00:25:17.040
Why, Phana?

00:25:17.780 --> 00:25:19.080
What the hell am I to you?

00:25:19.380 --> 00:25:20.640
You're my friend, you idiot!

00:25:22.030 --> 00:25:22.860
Friend?

00:25:24.480 --> 00:25:25.970
A friend wouldn't do this!

00:25:27.550 --> 00:25:29.580
If I had told you that Nawa's a merman,

00:25:30.400 --> 00:25:31.600
would you have believed me?

00:25:32.610 --> 00:25:33.660
Even if you did,

00:25:34.620 --> 00:25:36.460
do you think revealing this

00:25:36.900 --> 00:25:38.620
won't have any repercussions?

